summary:
In 2020 graduated cum laude as Bsc. in Chemical Engineering and Chemistry from University of Technology Eindhoven. In 2022, I did a graduation internship for 5 months at Shell in Amsterdam where I performed research on cryogenic heat exchangers for large-scale hydrogen liquefaction. In October 2022, I graduated as a Msc. in the field of Chemical Engineering with an average of 8.5/10.

As of January 2023, I work as second line chemical engineer for Envalior (previously for DSM Engineering Materials) at the DAB (diaminobutane) plant at the Chemelot site in Geleen. Here I am focussed on middle/long term projects. These projects vary from energy saving projects to projects that improve safety or security of supply.
